44bccbb.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcR8-L-haOVnakoq_MYjElJs50nttlUFPLVNCw";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:600;s:6:"height";i:600;s:6:"source";s:48:"https://ar.pinterest.com/pin/509680882800187108/";s:6:"domain";s:16:"ar.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:58:{i:0;s:136:"The Egg Chair was created in 1958 along with Jacobsens Swan Chair to furnish the lobby and lounges of the SAS Royal Hotel in Copenhagen.";i:1;s:102:"The organic oval shape of the chair was intended as a sculptural foil to the buildings angular design.";i:2;s:91:"The designers inventive reimagining of a traditional armchair is soft rounded and inviting.";i:3;s:66:"A similar design was the egg chair designed by Henrik Thor-Larsen.";i:4;s:87:"Known as the Ovalia Egg Chair this design came out ten years after the initial release.";i:5;s:88:"While it may not be the official egg chair it did receive a lot of attention in the 70s.";i:6;s:100:"It was even shown in the Men In Black movies along with appearances in TV shows like Mork and Mindy.";i:7;s:133:"The Egg Chair designed by Arne Jacobsen in 1957 owes its name to its organically shaped seat reminiscent as it is of a semi-open egg.";i:8;s:132:"Thanks to its generous seat the user can employ a variety of sitting positions and always benefit from the chairs considered design.";i:9;s:66:"Arne Jacobsens Iconic Egg Chair In Modern And Contemporary Design.";i:10;s:123:"Ever since it was designed by Arne Jacobsen in 1958 the Egg Chair was used to make spaces look sophisticated and beautiful.";i:11;s:95:"Its still very popular despite its age and thats all due to the design which is truly timeless.";i:12;s:221:"May 25 2019 - Modern elements of form and function are demonstrated with this Arne Jacobsen design known as the Egg Chair formally introduced as a signature Jacobsen chair for the Royal Hotel Copenhagen completed in 1961.";i:13;s:134:"Combining a modernist design concept with the 18th century traditional wing back chair design a refreshed modern idea may be realized.";i:14;s:26:"Design Arne Jacobsen 1958.";i:15;s:123:"Arne Jacobsen designed the Egg Chair and the Swan Chair for the lobby and reception areas in the Royal Hotel in Copenhagen.";i:16;s:190:"The commission to design every element of the hotel building as well as the furniture was Jacobsens grand opportunity to put his theories of integrated design and architecture into practice.";i:17;s:69:"The Jacobsen Egg Chair has become an icon in modern furniture design.";i:18;s:185:"Commissioned for the Royal Hotel in Copenhagen Denmark in 1958 the Egg Chairs wavelike shape demonstrates Jacobsens ingenuity to create furniture with a simple yet elegant construction.";i:19;s:71:"An elliptical upholstered chair called Ægget or as we know it the Egg.";i:20;s:70:"A velvet-covered Egg in Emma Jane Pilkingtons New York City apartment.";i:21;s:27:"Photo by Pascal Chevallier.";i:22;s:119:"The Ovalia Egg Pod chair has been around for decades and some even say that it is as old as the chicken and egg debate.";i:23;s:179:"The design is the brainchild of Henrik Thor-Larsen and it is based on the Aarnio Ball Chair with the uniqueness primarily resting on the fact that it looks distinctly like an egg.";i:24;s:95:"The Hanging Egg chair is a timeless design classic created by Nanna and Jørgen Ditzel in 1959.";i:25;s:151:"Today Hanging Egg is part of Sika-Designs Icons collection that features rattan furniture from some of the most talented designers of the 20th century.";i:26;s:69:"Hanging Egg is equally inviting in the living room childrens room or.";i:27;s:74:"Originally designed for the Radisson SAS hotel in Copenhagen back in 1958.";i:28;s:71:"Over the past 60 years the chair has grown into an iconic design chair.";i:29;s:77:"A typical characteristic of this design is the use of high-quality materials.";i:30;s:101:"Fritz Hansen Classics Campaign Enjoy a free Egg footstool with all Egg chairs until 31 December 2021.";i:31;s:4